From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 16:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] cmake: do not error on missing-field-initializers

The Level Zero loader headers provided by meta-intel (level-zero
1.31.0) are newer than the version this driver release targets and
introduce additional dispatch-table members. The driver leaves those
members default-initialized (nullptr) on purpose, which trips
-Wmissing-field-initializers (enabled via -Wextra) and, combined with
-Werror, breaks the build. Demote that specific warning so the driver
builds against the newer loader.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [oe specific]

Signed-off-by: Yogesh Tyagi <yogesh.tyagi@intel.com>
---
 cmake/compiler_flags.cmake | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/cmake/compiler_flags.cmake b/cmake/compiler_flags.cmake
index 0cc74c7..36a2425 100644
--- a/cmake/compiler_flags.cmake
+++ b/cmake/compiler_flags.cmake
@@ -5,6 +5,11 @@
 add_compile_options(
   # Compiler warnings
   -Wall -Wextra -Werror -Wno-unused-parameter -Wvla -Wno-error=cpp
+  # The Level Zero loader headers shipped by meta-intel are newer than
+  # the version this driver targets and add dispatch-table members that
+  # are intentionally left default-initialized (nullptr) here, so do not
+  # promote -Wmissing-field-initializers to an error.
+  -Wno-error=missing-field-initializers
   # Control flow integrity
   $<$<CONFIG:Release>:-fcf-protection=full>
   # Format string defence

-- 
